@node Introduction "Introduction to Mail"

Introduction to Mail

The purpose of Mail is to @{"display" MailPrimary} and manage mail folders containing Internet
style mail. It supports the @{"display" link MailItemWindow}, @{"printing" link CmdPrint}, and @{"logging" link CmdLog} of individual mail
items in folders, the @{"deletion" link CmdDelete} of mail items, and the @{"sending" link CmdNew} of mail to
Mailboxes.

There exist several other programs capable of doing this; however most of
these are Unix ports, and still show considerable signs of their ancestry.
Mail is an Amiga based program, and (mostly) adheres to the Amiga style
guide.  It is also @{"ARexx" link ARexx} capable, and has @{"context sensitive help" linkCmdHelp}
(ie the Help key works!).

Mail requires AmigaDOS 2.04 minimum. It can be used as a drop-in replacement
for any mailreader that uses standard uucp style mail folders (eg AmigaELM).

Also  distributed  with Mail are various utilities to support its use in an
AmiTCP environment.

Mail is written by @{"Graham Walter" link Author}.

@endnode

